======================================================================
AUTO-GENERATED INTERPRETATION PARAGRAPH
======================================================================

The superior performance of the 12-component ICA-GA model reflects a balance between
information retention and latent compactness. Of the 12 independent components, 12
showed statistically significant class separation across the 14 maturity levels after
Benjamini-Hochberg correction (q < 0.05). IC7 exhibited the strongest
discriminative power (η² = 0.635) and a Spearman correlation of
ρ = -0.238 with the ordered maturity index, suggesting a consistent
association with maturity progression. IC7 was primarily driven by spectral
markers around 1384, 1380, 1388, 1411, 1392 cm⁻¹, consistent with C-H bending / carboxylate stretch. The GA stage further refined
the latent representation by selectively retaining the most informative components;
IC2 was selected in 80% of GA runs, confirming its stable
discriminative contribution. Relative to the 32- and 53-component settings, the
12-component solution avoids the inclusion of weaker, noisier, or redundant latent
factors, thereby improving generalization and strengthening interpretability of the MIR
spectral signatures associated with strawberry maturity.

